<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1332,1538]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,271,1405,1429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Notes.</emphasis>
Authors of this paper noted the remarkable similarity of this large specimen with 
<taxonomicName box="[1188,1298,1405,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis box="[1188,1298,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">M. avidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<taxonomicName box="[1363,1436,1405,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis box="[1363,1436,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">avidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of species seems to be very homogeneous morphologically but highly diverse genetically, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[1294,1396,1441,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Merodon</taxonomicName>
sp. nova 
<number box="[214,228,1477,1501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2.0">2</number>
</emphasis>
, although very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[525,637,1477,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis box="[525,637,1477,1501]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">M. avidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is much larger, thus making it one of the most distinctive taxa in the group (Ante Vujiċ in lit.). Larva undescribed.
</paragraph>
